        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="103" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Disables or restores the <bpt id="p1">[</bpt>/RTC<ept id="p1">](../build/reference/rtc-run-time-error-checks.md)</ept> settings.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="104" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Syntax</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="105" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Remarks</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="106" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>You cannot enable a run-time check that was not enabled with a compiler option.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="107" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>For example, if you do not specify /RTCs, specifying <ph id="ph1">`#pragma runtime_checks( "s", restore)`</ph> will not enable stack frame verification.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="108" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>The <bpt id="p1">**</bpt>runtime_checks<ept id="p1">**</ept> pragma must appear outside a function and takes effect at the first function defined after the pragma is seen.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="109" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>The <bpt id="p1">**</bpt>restore<ept id="p1">**</ept> and <bpt id="p2">**</bpt>off<ept id="p2">**</ept> arguments turn options specified in the <bpt id="p3">*</bpt>runtime_checks<ept id="p3">*</ept> on or off.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="110" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>The <bpt id="p1">*</bpt>runtime_checks<ept id="p1">*</ept> can be zero or more of the parameters shown in the following table.</source>
        </trans-unit>
